images.name: Penn Powers Past Dartmouth  - Via Ivy League
images.caption: Max Martz paced Penn with 13 points on the afternoon, one of five Quakers in double figures

article.linkText: Williams, Martz lead balanced Penn past Dartmouth 78-68
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- — Jelani Williams and Max Martz scored 13 points each to lead Penn to a 78-68 win over Dartmouth on Saturday. George Smith added 12 points and five assists for the Quakers (6-11, 3-1 Ivy League). Jordan Dingle had 11 points. Clark Slajchert also had 11. Brendan Barr scored 16 points for Dartmouth (4-10, 1-2). Aaryn Rai had 11. Dame Adelekun grabbed 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25
